<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFF80FF43FF4A881EE342FEBC" lastPageId="82" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FF80FF43FF4A881EE342FEBC" blockId="81.[151,1437,1764,2043]" lastBlockId="82.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="82" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF80FF40FF4A881EE67EF8E7" bold="true" box="[199,308,1836,1862]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Remarks</emphasis>
. The placement of this species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF80FF40FD25881FE5AEF8E7" authorityName="Lilljeborg" authorityYear="1865" box="[680,740,1837,1862]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF80FF40FD25881FE5AEF8E7" box="[680,740,1837,1862]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been reviewed, mostly because of the few and rather poor illustrations. Since its description (
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FF80FF40FDD88862E5AEF8CB" author="Walker, A. O." box="[597,740,1872,1898]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="229 - 300" refId="ref50631" refString="Walker, A. O. (1904) Report on the Amphipoda collected by Professor Herdman, at Ceylon, in 1902. Ceylon Pearl Oyster Fisheries, Supplementary Reports, 17, 229 - 300." type="journal article" year="1904">Walker 1904</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF80FF40FD7E8863E4E0F8CB" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1904" box="[755,938,1872,1898]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF80FF40FD7E8863E4E0F8CB" box="[755,938,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tiron thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has appeared in the literature mainly in keys to 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF80FF40FF3B8847E7B8F82F" authorityName="Lilljeborg" authorityYear="1865" box="[182,242,1909,1934]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF80FF40FF3B8847E7B8F82F" box="[182,242,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, separated out on account of an unusual outer plate of the maxilliped. The present review of the tironins makes it possible to compare this species with others in the currently recognised genera.According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FF80FF40FB7188AAE2D6F813" author="Walker, A. O." box="[1276,1436,1944,1970]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="229 - 300" refId="ref50631" refString="Walker, A. O. (1904) Report on the Amphipoda collected by Professor Herdman, at Ceylon, in 1902. Ceylon Pearl Oyster Fisheries, Supplementary Reports, 17, 229 - 300." type="journal article" year="1904">Walker (1904)</bibRefCitation>
the species has a short, moderately curved and distally widening gnathopod 1 basis similar to species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF80FF40FAA6888FE2DFF877" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[1323,1429,1981,2006]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF80FF40FAA6888FE2DFF877" box="[1323,1429,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, contrasting with the elongate, straight gnathopod 1 basis of equal width throughout found in all other tironins. Fur- thermore the species has stubby pereopods 3–7 (although poorly illustrated), and unusual, concave maxillipedal outer plates closely similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF83FF43FE7E8F89E58FFF74" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Hirayama" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[499,709,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galeatus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF83FF43FE7E8F89E58FFF74" box="[499,709,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Minitiron galeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF83FF43FC838F89E41BFF74" box="[782,849,187,213]" name="Japan" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Although many details remain to be learned about Walker’s 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF83FF43FE8E8FEDE6F6FF58" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1904" box="[259,444,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF83FF43FE8E8FEDE6F6FF58" box="[259,444,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Tiron thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, notably the 
<typeStatus id="54AD0BA3FF83FF43FDDF8FEDE5C8FF58" box="[594,642,223,249]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
of setal spines on the outer plate spine-row and shape and size of the inner plate of maxilla 1, the species is here tentatively transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF83FF43FC1A8E31E34BFEBD" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[919,1025,259,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF83FF43FC1A8E31E34BFEBD" box="[919,1025,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
